      {
        "id": 4596943,
        "name": "Brad Baker",
        "username": "Brad_Baker",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/brad_baker/{size}/663_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-02-17T16:46:54.543Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019m trying to remember when they officially split.  Early 2022 is when I recall hearing a decent amount of talk about it.  I don\u2019t know what level of involvement Fabrice had in the \u2018Agrapart\u2019 wines, but since at least the mid-2000s, I believe it was mostly related to ownership and being a share holder.  At some point, after Pascal came to be the lead for the family business, it didn\u2019t sit well with Fabrice and plans to divide the estate began.  Family bickering or battles are not uncommon with smaller Champagne producers.  Godme, Billiot, Marie-Noelle Ledru, Seleque, Pierre Peters etc\u2026 are all examples of this.  Sometimes things worked out and a solution found, other times, the domaine split things up and each side went their own way.</p>",
